  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why won't IFTTT link to my tumblr account?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why IFTTT (If This Then That) won't link to your Tumblr account. Here are some common issues and troubleshooting steps you can take:\n\n1. **Authorization Issues**: Make sure that you have authorized IFTTT to access your Tumblr account. Try disconnecting and then reconnecting your Tumblr account in the IFTTT settings.\n\n2. **Account Privacy Settings**: If your Tumblr blog is private, it may prevent IFTTT from accessing it. You could try setting your blog to public to see if that resolves the issue.\n\n3. **Incorrect Login Credentials**: Ensure that you are entering the correct username and password for your Tumblr account. You may want to log in to Tumblr separately to verify your credentials.\n\n4. **Two-Factor Authentication**: If your Tumblr account has two-factor authentication enabled, it might complicate the authorization process. Check if this is the case and see if you need to create a special password for IFTTT.\n\n5. **Outdated App**: Ensure that you are using the latest version of IFTTT. If there\u2019s an update available, install it, as it may contain fixes for integration issues.\n\n6. **IFTTT Service Issues**: Sometimes, the issue could be on IFTTT\u2019s end. Check their status page or social media accounts for any outages or ongoing issues with the Tumblr integration.\n\n7. **Browser Issues**: If you are linking your Tumblr account through a web browser, try using a different browser or clearing your current browser's cache and cookies.\n\n8. **Check for Existing Connections**: If you have previously connected Tumblr to IFTTT, make sure there are no conflicts with multiple connections or automations that might be causing issues.\n\nIf you've tried these steps and continue to have problems, consider reaching out to IFTTT support for further assistance.",
